{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\nThe single `state[\"signature\"]` slot is last-writer-wins, so one kind clobbers another.\nThis is the root-cause fix and the riskiest slice (back-compat + compaction), done first.\n## What\nReplace the slot with `state[\"attestations\"]`, a kind-keyed map applied per-key-LWW like\n`process_workflow_run`. `process_signature` routes by `data[\"kind\"]` (fallback: parse\n`manifest[0]`). New code writes ONLY `attestations` into compiled state and never writes\n`state[\"signature\"]` into events. Read fold-in: a ticket/snapshot carrying only the legacy\n`signature` is folded into `attestations` on read (kind from its manifest). SNAPSHOT mirror:\na NEW snapshot ALSO synthesizes a legacy `signature` (= most-recent attestation) for\nold/rolled-back clones; the mirror is kept PERMANENTLY in this epic (dropping it is the\ndeferred contract-phase follow-up). Also add `state[\"last_reopened_at\"]`: the reducer records\nthe timestamp of the most recent `closed -> open` transition (today `process_status` writes\nonly `state[\"status\"]`), so `compute_validity` can check \"not reopened since signed_at\"\npurely from compiled state.\n## Scope\n`src/rebar/reducer/_processors.py` (`process_signature`, `process_status` for\n`last_reopened_at`, `process_snapshot` fold-in + mirror), `src/rebar/_commands/compact.py`\n(synthesize mirror), `ticket_state.schema.json`. No change to the signed payload.\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `attestations` map replaces the single slot; additive across kinds, replace within a kind; routing by `data[\"kind\"]` with `manifest[0]` fallback.\n- [ ] New code never writes `state[\"signature\"]` into events; legacy single `signature` folded into `attestations` on read.\n- [ ] New SNAPSHOTs synthesize a legacy `signature` mirror (most-recent attestation); kept permanently here.\n- [ ] `state[\"last_reopened_at\"]` records the most recent closed->open transition timestamp (null if never reopened).\n- [ ] Compaction/SNAPSHOT round-trips all kinds; empty `attestations` omitted from `show`/state.\n## Added (review)\n- Update `src/rebar/reducer/_present.py` `_INTERNAL_SUBKEYS` IN THIS STORY (the one that\n  introduces the two-level `attestations.<kind>` shape) to strip the HMAC hex at\n  `attestations.<kind>.signature`, so there is no leak window between this merge and ed26.\n- [ ] HMAC hex never appears in `show`/MCP output for any attestation kind (closed in 114f)."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1782785605850837001,"uuid":"ec38d5b6-9833-4c02-8acf-0d03ec814584"}